{{Chinese name|[[Wu (surname)|Wu (吳)]]}}
'''Jihan Wu''' ({{zh |s=吳忌寒}}) is a co-founder of [[Bitmain]] (with [[Micree Zhan]]), and a prominent supporter of [[Bitcoin Cash]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fastcompany.com/40447293/growing-pains-for-bitcoin-as-rival-factions-split-the-currency-in-two|title=Growing Pains For Bitcoin As Rival Factions Split The Currency In Two|date=1 August 2017|publisher=}}</ref> He was ranked one of the ten most influential figures in the blockchain world by Coindesk in 2017. <ref name=coindesk>{{cite web|url=https://www.coindesk.com/coindesk-most-influential-2017-10-jihan-wu/|title=CoinDesk's Most Influential in Blockchain 2017: Jihan Wu|date=31 December 2017|publisher=}}</ref>

In 2018 he was ranked number 3 in Fortune's The Ledger 40 under 40<ref name=Fortune>{{cite web|url=http://fortune.com/the-ledger-40-under-40/jihan-wu-3/|title=Fortune The Ledger 40 under 40: Jihan Wu|date=29 July 2018|publisher=}}</ref> for transforming business at the leading edge of finance and technology. His net worth in 2018 was [[United States dollar|US$]]$2.39 billion.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.moneymakers.com/crypto-billionaires-china/ |title=Crypto Billionaires On The Rise In China Despite Crypto Ban |last=Datta |first=Deepan |date=2018-10-15 |access-date=2018-11-08 |language=en-US}}</ref>

Wu lives in China and has an economics degree from [[Peking University]].<ref name=coindesk />

