{{Infobox Museum |name = Safir Office Machines Museum |image = Safir Office Machines Museum.JPG |location = Iransahr Street, [[Tehran]], [[Iran]]{{Flag icon|Iran}} |visitors = |established = 2008 |website = http://www.officemuseum.ir/ |president = Farshad Kamalkhani }}
The '''Safir Office Machines Museum''' is a private museum located in [[Tehran]], [[Iran]]. It was founded in 2008 by Frashad Kamalkhani, the museum owner. It includes a collection of early office machines.
==Collection== There are more than 80 unique and early devices such as [[typewriter]]s, check writers, [[pencil sharpener]]s, [[duplicating machines|duplicators]], [[calculator]]s, [[cash register]]s, [[telegraph]] equipment, [[telephone]]s, etc., in the collection.
